The paper deals with graph theory and algorithms, which are typically categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The study of twinless strongly connected graphs and related problems involves combinatorial and geometric aspects, which are covered by cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper presents an algorithm for computing connected components, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
